1
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:42,720
Because I'm not his real son,

2
00:02:42,800 --> 00:02:44,240
that makes me the villain?

3
00:02:44,320 --> 00:02:46,640
And a rebellious son like you

4
00:02:46,720 --> 00:02:48,800
and that woman
who'd do anything for money,

5
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:51,120
aren't you both also the suspicious ones?

6
00:02:51,200 --> 00:02:53,160
Don't think I don't know
what you did to Dad.

7
00:02:53,240 --> 00:02:54,240
What did I do?!

8
00:02:54,320 --> 00:02:56,440
You pushed Dad down the stairs.

9
00:03:00,600 --> 00:03:03,240
<i>I only cared about myself.</i>

10
00:03:03,320 --> 00:03:06,120
<i>I kept blaming Dad for hurting me.</i>

11
00:03:06,640 --> 00:03:08,160
<i>But in the end, it was me</i>

12
00:03:08,720 --> 00:03:10,560
who kept hurting him all along.

13
00:03:11,160 --> 00:03:12,920
I've never wished you harm,

14
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:14,880
now or ever.

15
00:03:15,520 --> 00:03:17,240
I'm on your side.

16
00:03:17,320 --> 00:03:18,560
Excuse me.

17
00:03:19,960 --> 00:03:21,240
Dad, you know who did it?

18
00:03:23,560 --> 00:03:24,680
Was it Rachen?

19
00:03:54,520 --> 00:03:55,520
Yes.

20
00:04:01,520 --> 00:04:02,400
Mr. Trai,

21
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:05,280
the forensic police called.

22
00:04:20,240 --> 00:04:21,959
The autopsy results are out.

23
00:04:22,040 --> 00:04:25,200
Mr. Tritot died from asphyxiation,

24
00:04:25,280 --> 00:04:26,360
just as we suspected.

25
00:04:27,120 --> 00:04:28,800
As for the CCTV footage,

26
00:04:29,320 --> 00:04:31,560
like I mentioned before, a skilled hacker

27
00:04:31,640 --> 00:04:33,440
broke into the hospital's

28
00:04:33,520 --> 00:04:35,040
security system,

29
00:04:35,120 --> 00:04:37,160
so there's no recorded footage at all.

30
00:04:38,160 --> 00:04:40,560
We're trying to recover it.

31
00:04:42,640 --> 00:04:44,520
You said there was progress with the case?

32
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:46,200
Yes.

33
00:04:46,280 --> 00:04:48,120
We've arrested
the kid who stole your phone.

34
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:55,160
How old are you?

35
00:04:55,760 --> 00:04:57,360
Someone ordered you to do this, right?

36
00:04:58,360 --> 00:04:59,600
How much did they pay you?

37
00:05:00,760 --> 00:05:02,200
You only ever talk about money.

38
00:05:04,200 --> 00:05:05,800
Then if they didn't hire you,

39
00:05:06,400 --> 00:05:07,520
what did they promise you?

40
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:09,280
That they'd get revenge for you?

41
00:05:13,800 --> 00:05:14,640
I'm sorry.

42
00:05:15,880 --> 00:05:17,320
I'm sorry on behalf of everyone.

43
00:05:17,920 --> 00:05:19,840
You must've suffered a lot
because of Be Rich.

44
00:05:24,040 --> 00:05:26,640
Right now, someone is using your pain

45
00:05:26,720 --> 00:05:28,040
to destroy Be Rich.

46
00:05:28,680 --> 00:05:30,040
But are you sure

47
00:05:31,080 --> 00:05:33,120
you're not destroying your own life too?

48
00:05:33,960 --> 00:05:36,000
Conspiracy to commit premeditated murder

49
00:05:36,080 --> 00:05:37,360
can ruin your entire future.

50
00:05:37,440 --> 00:05:40,280
Are you really going to throw
the rest of your life away for this?

51
00:05:40,960 --> 00:05:42,760
You've suffered enough.

52
00:05:44,360 --> 00:05:46,200
Don't take all the responsibility alone.

53
00:05:49,120 --> 00:05:50,360
Who ordered you to do this?

54
00:05:55,320 --> 00:05:56,960
The rest of my life?

55
00:05:57,800 --> 00:05:59,760
A future?

56
00:05:59,840 --> 00:06:02,400
- It was already ruined by you people!
- Sit down.

57
00:06:02,480 --> 00:06:04,240
You killed my dad!

58
00:06:04,320 --> 00:06:06,040
You killed my dad!

59
00:06:06,560 --> 00:06:07,840
You killed my dad!

60
00:06:07,920 --> 00:06:09,640
My life's ruined because of you!

61
00:06:16,760 --> 00:06:18,920
‪Here. He's Mr. Bodin, or Bomb,

62
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:20,040
son of Mr. Bandit,

63
00:06:20,120 --> 00:06:22,640
a Be Rich loan customer from last year.

64
00:06:22,720 --> 00:06:24,800
Bandit worked at a factory, clean record.

65
00:06:24,880 --> 00:06:27,680
But after health issues,
he couldn't pay the loan back on time.

66
00:06:28,280 --> 00:06:30,600
Our company sent debt collectors.

67
00:06:31,200 --> 00:06:34,000
It seems he was under extreme stress
and collapsed, unconscious.

68
00:06:34,080 --> 00:06:35,280
The report says

69
00:06:35,360 --> 00:06:37,800
he died in a workplace accident.

70
00:06:39,480 --> 00:06:41,360
Then he didn't die because of Be Rich.

71
00:06:41,880 --> 00:06:43,720
And he blames Be Rich
for killing his father?

72
00:06:44,360 --> 00:06:45,360
Be Rich may have done it.

73
00:06:45,880 --> 00:06:48,640
Directly or indirectly,
money can kill either way.

74
00:06:59,840 --> 00:07:01,320
Rest in peace, Tritot.

75
00:07:02,160 --> 00:07:03,760
Don't worry about things here.

76
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:05,960
I'll take care

77
00:07:07,080 --> 00:07:08,480
of the rest.

78
00:07:13,440 --> 00:07:14,880
Our condolences, Rachen.

79
00:07:16,320 --> 00:07:18,320
Mr. Tritot looked so strong.

80
00:07:18,400 --> 00:07:19,520
He shouldn't have left so soon.

81
00:07:20,320 --> 00:07:21,960
He had a heart condition.

82
00:07:26,360 --> 00:07:28,360
Did Mr. Tritot leave any final words?

83
00:07:31,120 --> 00:07:32,640
Sorry for being so direct,

84
00:07:32,720 --> 00:07:34,640
but you know what I'm worried about.

85
00:07:36,560 --> 00:07:38,960
Let's discuss it after the funeral.

86
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:47,840
I understand

87
00:07:47,920 --> 00:07:49,840
you want to mourn your father,

88
00:07:49,920 --> 00:07:52,360
but you're the only one

89
00:07:52,440 --> 00:07:54,240
who can carry on his work.

90
00:07:54,840 --> 00:07:57,480
If you want your father
to rest peacefully,

91
00:07:58,080 --> 00:07:59,760
you should make Be Rich

92
00:07:59,840 --> 00:08:01,280
become more prosperous, greater,

93
00:08:01,920 --> 00:08:04,000
and wealthier than ever.

94
00:08:05,680 --> 00:08:07,680
But that so-called wealth and greatness

95
00:08:08,760 --> 00:08:09,800
killed our father, Rachen.

96
00:08:12,360 --> 00:08:13,840
You just arrived
and are already causing trouble,

97
00:08:14,640 --> 00:08:16,600
even at your own father's funeral.

98
00:08:17,840 --> 00:08:20,040
You're always making
a grand entrance, as usual.

99
00:08:20,640 --> 00:08:23,680
What is it? Afraid your father's funeral
might be too quiet?

100
00:08:23,760 --> 00:08:24,640
Or…

101
00:08:25,240 --> 00:08:26,640
afraid someone else
might end up better off than you?

102
00:08:28,880 --> 00:08:33,080
If this is a game of musical chairs
you're all enjoying, don't worry.

103
00:08:34,200 --> 00:08:37,679
I won't play.
I don't want to become like Dad.

104
00:08:38,400 --> 00:08:39,520
Trai.

105
00:08:40,720 --> 00:08:43,640
This is Dad's funeral.
I don't want to fight with you.

106
00:08:44,560 --> 00:08:46,240
Then let's talk outside.

107
00:09:04,520 --> 00:09:05,840
What's your problem now?

108
00:09:07,200 --> 00:09:08,680
I went to the police station.

109
00:09:08,760 --> 00:09:10,920
They still haven't caught
the person who did it,

110
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:14,400
but it's obvious, Dad died
because of people who hate Be Rich.

111
00:09:14,480 --> 00:09:16,160
They want revenge on us.

112
00:09:17,600 --> 00:09:18,760
Revenge?

113
00:09:18,840 --> 00:09:20,600
You make it sound like Be Rich
went around robbing and killing people.

114
00:09:21,280 --> 00:09:22,840
High-interest loans.

115
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:26,080
Sending people to aggressively collect
debts. Threatening them with the law.

116
00:09:26,720 --> 00:09:29,440
Docking interest from their salaries
until they barely had money left to eat.

117
00:09:30,040 --> 00:09:33,600
Seizing their assets and reselling them
until they were completely ruined.

118
00:09:34,200 --> 00:09:36,480
Be Rich's policies, obsessed only with
hitting targets and maximizing profit,

119
00:09:36,560 --> 00:09:38,000
are killing them indirectly.

120
00:09:38,080 --> 00:09:40,040
- Have you ever thought about that?
- Them?

121
00:09:40,120 --> 00:09:41,200
Them? Them?

122
00:09:41,280 --> 00:09:42,480
What about us, Trai?

123
00:09:42,560 --> 00:09:44,600
Be Rich doesn't make profit

124
00:09:44,680 --> 00:09:46,960
for me, for Dad,

125
00:09:47,680 --> 00:09:48,880
or for the executives.

126
00:09:48,960 --> 00:09:51,200
But we have hundreds

127
00:09:51,280 --> 00:09:53,360
of employees.

128
00:09:53,440 --> 00:09:57,000
They have families,
children, parents to take care of too.

129
00:09:57,080 --> 00:09:58,640
Have you forgotten that?

130
00:09:59,240 --> 00:10:02,720
Damn it. I never thought I'd have to argue
with you about this right now.

131
00:10:03,320 --> 00:10:06,560
Dad is still lying inside there.
But instead of feeling remorse or grief,

132
00:10:06,640 --> 00:10:07,920
you're worried about other people?

133
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:10,480
I just want you to see
the real root cause.

134
00:10:11,080 --> 00:10:12,040
But for me,

135
00:10:12,120 --> 00:10:14,680
the real reason Dad died was you!

136
00:10:15,840 --> 00:10:16,680
Remember that!

137
00:11:19,680 --> 00:11:22,440
Mr. Trai looks so lonely.

138
00:11:23,240 --> 00:11:24,920
In an atmosphere like this,

139
00:11:26,360 --> 00:11:28,400
no wonder he doesn't want to stay.

140
00:11:54,280 --> 00:11:55,280
Dad…

141
00:11:58,080 --> 00:11:59,840
Do you think like Rachen does?

142
00:12:02,600 --> 00:12:04,280
That everything is my fault?

143
00:12:12,800 --> 00:12:14,600
You're not really gone, right?

144
00:12:17,360 --> 00:12:18,840
You're still with me, right?

145
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:22,960
No light from Dad.

146
00:12:25,400 --> 00:12:27,080
No starlight from Mom.

147
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:32,960
I have no one.

148
00:12:54,360 --> 00:12:55,960
Come here, follow me.

149
00:12:56,040 --> 00:12:57,600
- Ugh.
- This table goes right here.

150
00:12:57,680 --> 00:12:59,840
- Yes.
- Hey, be careful with that.

151
00:12:59,920 --> 00:13:01,400
- Here, here.
- Be careful.

152
00:13:01,480 --> 00:13:03,040
- Yeah.
- Alright.

153
00:13:03,120 --> 00:13:04,400
- Yeah.
- Put it down.

154
00:13:04,480 --> 00:13:05,680
Alright.

155
00:13:05,760 --> 00:13:08,240
Oh, seems like we don't have chairs yet.

156
00:13:08,320 --> 00:13:09,160
I'll go grab them.

157
00:13:09,240 --> 00:13:10,480
Oh, no, Kanah, don't.

158
00:13:10,560 --> 00:13:11,680
Your asthma might flare up.

159
00:13:11,760 --> 00:13:13,040
Hey, Niu.

160
00:13:13,120 --> 00:13:15,360
I'm not that weak.

161
00:13:15,440 --> 00:13:16,600
Stop arguing.

162
00:13:16,680 --> 00:13:17,840
I've got them.

163
00:13:19,880 --> 00:13:21,120
What's going on here?

164
00:13:22,960 --> 00:13:24,160
Friends.

165
00:13:28,520 --> 00:13:30,000
Your friends.

166
00:13:30,080 --> 00:13:32,320
You're not alone, Mr. Trai.

167
00:13:38,920 --> 00:13:41,960
Mr. Trai, come eat pork barbecue
with us. Come on.

168
00:14:17,480 --> 00:14:19,480
Oh, Rachen.

169
00:14:23,960 --> 00:14:25,200
Dad…

170
00:14:25,720 --> 00:14:27,200
Still not going home?

171
00:14:29,040 --> 00:14:31,000
You're working late again?

172
00:14:33,200 --> 00:14:34,480
Take care of your health too.

173
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:37,680
Pulling all-nighters like this,
you'll get sick.

174
00:14:38,280 --> 00:14:40,080
You came back to me, didn't you?

175
00:14:43,640 --> 00:14:46,920
I'm right here. I never went anywhere.

176
00:14:50,040 --> 00:14:51,720
I miss you, Dad.

177
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:38,720
I miss you, Dad…

178
00:15:42,200 --> 00:15:44,880
Can you come back and stay with me?

179
00:15:53,040 --> 00:15:56,040
I miss you, Dad…

180
00:16:00,440 --> 00:16:02,520
I miss you…

181
00:16:06,120 --> 00:16:07,080
Dad…

182
00:16:07,160 --> 00:16:08,400
It's boiling. Veggies!

183
00:16:08,480 --> 00:16:09,760
- Put the veggies in.
- Put them in.

184
00:16:09,840 --> 00:16:10,680
Corn too. More corn.

185
00:16:10,760 --> 00:16:12,480
- It's hot.
- Yeah, that's it!

186
00:16:12,560 --> 00:16:13,760
They're make the broth sweet.

187
00:16:13,840 --> 00:16:14,720
Glass noodles?

188
00:16:14,800 --> 00:16:15,800
- Bring it.
- Pour it in.

189
00:16:17,120 --> 00:16:18,520
This crispy bacon,

190
00:16:18,600 --> 00:16:21,040
I took really good care of it for you.

191
00:16:21,120 --> 00:16:22,640
Kanah almost stole it.

192
00:16:23,320 --> 00:16:25,360
Hey, Bung.

193
00:16:25,880 --> 00:16:28,280
I wasn't stealing.
I was helping you grill it.

194
00:16:28,360 --> 00:16:29,200
Wow,

195
00:16:29,280 --> 00:16:31,480
a good deed still gets punished, huh?

196
00:16:31,560 --> 00:16:34,200
Garlic fried rice is here.

197
00:16:34,880 --> 00:16:37,440
- I remember you like it, Mr. Trai.
- Hey, enough grilling.

198
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:40,200
And this, bouncy pork.

199
00:16:40,280 --> 00:16:41,720
I added corn

200
00:16:41,800 --> 00:16:43,200
for extra fiber.

201
00:16:43,280 --> 00:16:44,680
Yeah.

202
00:16:44,760 --> 00:16:48,000
And have some hot soup too,
so it goes down easier.

203
00:16:48,080 --> 00:16:50,520
Put it in, put it all in.

204
00:16:50,600 --> 00:16:52,520
Whoa, Trai, look.

205
00:16:52,600 --> 00:16:55,200
This shrimp is huge.

206
00:16:55,280 --> 00:16:58,720
Super bouncy! Trai!

207
00:16:58,800 --> 00:17:01,160
Take it. So sweet.

208
00:17:01,240 --> 00:17:03,720
Yeah.

209
00:17:10,920 --> 00:17:12,119
Want some veggies?

210
00:17:12,200 --> 00:17:13,440
Yeah, veggies too.

211
00:17:13,520 --> 00:17:15,640
- Yeah.
- Lots of them.

212
00:17:15,720 --> 00:17:17,119
Yeah.

213
00:17:17,200 --> 00:17:18,119
For your health, Mr. Trai.

214
00:17:18,200 --> 00:17:20,319
- Alright.
- Lots of veggies.

215
00:17:20,400 --> 00:17:21,680
Alright.

216
00:17:21,760 --> 00:17:23,079
Here, Trai.

217
00:17:24,680 --> 00:17:27,160
- Do you want anything else?
- Do you want anything else?

218
00:17:30,720 --> 00:17:33,240
I'm… not very hungry.

219
00:17:35,520 --> 00:17:37,640
Even if you're not hungry,
you have to eat.

220
00:17:37,720 --> 00:17:38,800
You need strength to keep going.

221
00:17:39,760 --> 00:17:41,000
Yeah.

222
00:17:41,720 --> 00:17:42,760
Look.

223
00:17:42,840 --> 00:17:44,200
Even the bacon

224
00:17:44,280 --> 00:17:46,720
is giving its all and is still sizzling.

225
00:17:48,040 --> 00:17:49,080
Sizzle on.

226
00:17:49,160 --> 00:17:50,680
Sizzle on.

227
00:17:50,760 --> 00:17:51,640
Sizzle on.

228
00:17:51,720 --> 00:17:53,200
Sizzle on.

229
00:17:53,280 --> 00:17:54,240
Sizzle on.

230
00:17:55,160 --> 00:17:56,600
- Sizzle on.
- Sizzle on.

231
00:18:02,400 --> 00:18:03,320
Thank you.

232
00:18:03,840 --> 00:18:05,360
Thank you so much, everyone.

233
00:18:07,200 --> 00:18:09,920
If you're thanking us,
you have to finish all of it.

234
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:12,160
You've barely eaten for days.

235
00:18:26,920 --> 00:18:29,240
- Amazing!
- But that bite was a bit small, Mr. Trai.

236
00:18:29,320 --> 00:18:30,400
Eat more.

237
00:18:30,480 --> 00:18:32,920
- Trai, here.
- Eat more.

238
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:35,640
- Bacon too.
- Sauce too.

239
00:18:36,240 --> 00:18:37,960
Yeah.

240
00:18:38,040 --> 00:18:40,200
Shrimp head too.

241
00:18:40,280 --> 00:18:41,520
It's edible.

242
00:18:46,560 --> 00:18:47,560
What?

243
00:18:48,080 --> 00:18:49,520
Dad left all his shares to me?

244
00:18:50,120 --> 00:18:51,640
Yes. All the Be Rich shares

245
00:18:52,240 --> 00:18:53,400
under Mr. Tritot's name

246
00:18:53,480 --> 00:18:55,480
were intended
to be given to you, Mr. Trai,

247
00:18:56,080 --> 00:18:57,400
along with this house as well.

248
00:18:58,160 --> 00:19:01,480
As for the remaining assets, real estate,

249
00:19:01,560 --> 00:19:03,160
land, cash,

250
00:19:03,240 --> 00:19:05,360
and gold kept at the bank,

251
00:19:05,440 --> 00:19:07,880
they will be distributed
according to the details provided.

252
00:19:25,040 --> 00:19:26,120
Counselor.

253
00:19:29,560 --> 00:19:31,720
Are you sure the will you read

254
00:19:31,800 --> 00:19:32,760
is the latest version?

255
00:19:33,360 --> 00:19:34,200
Yes.

256
00:19:34,280 --> 00:19:36,000
Mr. Tritot made it just last month.

257
00:19:41,280 --> 00:19:42,240
And…

258
00:19:43,520 --> 00:19:45,720
Mr. Tritot didn't…

259
00:19:56,200 --> 00:19:58,720
He didn't list my name in the will at all?

260
00:20:02,120 --> 00:20:03,320
I'm truly sorry.

261
00:20:03,840 --> 00:20:07,000
I only carried out Mr. Tritot's wishes.

262
00:20:23,120 --> 00:20:25,360
Tritot gave all his shares to Trai?

263
00:20:26,200 --> 00:20:27,760
How many shares did he have?

264
00:20:27,840 --> 00:20:29,360
30%, ma'am.

265
00:20:29,440 --> 00:20:31,760
Mr. Trai originally had 15%.

266
00:20:31,840 --> 00:20:34,200
So now he's at 45%.

267
00:20:34,960 --> 00:20:36,120
That's still not half.

268
00:20:36,720 --> 00:20:38,680
But if you add the 10% Rachen holds,

269
00:20:39,280 --> 00:20:40,200
the Bowornmongkolphongs

270
00:20:40,280 --> 00:20:42,280
will still monopolize power
in the company.

271
00:20:43,560 --> 00:20:45,520
But Rachen and Trai don't get along.

272
00:20:45,600 --> 00:20:47,200
They won't join hands, right, Mom?

273
00:20:47,280 --> 00:20:50,600
In any industry,
you can't trust people, Mika.

274
00:20:53,880 --> 00:20:55,360
You can only trust money.

275
00:20:56,120 --> 00:20:57,720
Are you going to buy Mr. Rachen?

276
00:21:01,960 --> 00:21:03,200
Rachen.

277
00:21:04,160 --> 00:21:05,360
Let's talk.

278
00:21:06,680 --> 00:21:07,680
Stop.

279
00:21:08,640 --> 00:21:09,720
What do you want from me now?

280
00:21:10,480 --> 00:21:12,320
There has to be a reason
Dad gave me the shares.

281
00:21:12,960 --> 00:21:14,320
A reason?

282
00:21:14,400 --> 00:21:16,800
It's simple, because you're his real son.

283
00:21:16,880 --> 00:21:19,080
Dad was a businessman.

284
00:21:19,160 --> 00:21:21,080
He calculated everything
in financial terms.

285
00:21:21,160 --> 00:21:22,240
And when it comes to the company,

286
00:21:22,320 --> 00:21:25,200
of course he'd value profit
more than blood.

287
00:21:25,800 --> 00:21:28,400
What are you trying to imply?

288
00:21:28,480 --> 00:21:29,680
That Dad didn't trust me,

289
00:21:29,760 --> 00:21:30,640
so he didn't give me shares?

290
00:21:30,720 --> 00:21:33,000
No. I don't know.
That's why I'm asking you.

291
00:21:33,080 --> 00:21:34,600
Well, you won already, didn't you?

292
00:21:34,680 --> 00:21:35,960
You got everything.

293
00:21:36,600 --> 00:21:38,360
Shares. The company.

294
00:21:38,960 --> 00:21:40,320
Dad's love.

295
00:21:40,400 --> 00:21:41,560
What else do you want?

296
00:21:41,640 --> 00:21:43,880
Someone deliberately murdered our dad.

297
00:21:44,480 --> 00:21:46,840
I don't know who yet,
but it's tied to Be Rich for sure.

298
00:21:47,680 --> 00:21:49,480
Maybe Dad wanted me to investigate this.

299
00:21:51,680 --> 00:21:52,840
So in the end,

300
00:21:53,720 --> 00:21:55,320
Dad still didn't trust me.

301
00:21:56,080 --> 00:21:58,240
And look, another thing you got.

302
00:21:58,320 --> 00:22:01,160
Dad's trust, he trusted you.

303
00:22:01,680 --> 00:22:04,720
You got everything without having
to struggle for a damn thing.

304
00:22:04,800 --> 00:22:06,280
But me,

305
00:22:07,120 --> 00:22:08,680
eighteen years.

306
00:22:08,760 --> 00:22:10,680
Eighteen years I lived with Dad.

307
00:22:11,280 --> 00:22:13,160
There wasn't a single day I didn't try.

308
00:22:13,240 --> 00:22:15,280
I fought, so he'd see me,

309
00:22:15,360 --> 00:22:16,400
so he'd accept me.

310
00:22:17,000 --> 00:22:18,280
And in the end, what happened?

311
00:22:21,200 --> 00:22:22,400
Dad still didn't choose me.

312
00:22:47,200 --> 00:22:48,960
Why did you do this to me, Dad?

313
00:23:01,320 --> 00:23:02,840
Is this your house?

314
00:23:09,520 --> 00:23:11,360
From now on, it'll be our house.

315
00:23:14,480 --> 00:23:15,600
Thank you.

316
00:23:33,920 --> 00:23:35,080
Dad,

317
00:23:37,880 --> 00:23:40,040
I have something to show you.

318
00:23:49,600 --> 00:23:50,960
Very good. Very good.

319
00:23:52,640 --> 00:23:53,480
Good job.

320
00:23:54,800 --> 00:23:56,640
That's my boy.

321
00:24:02,720 --> 00:24:04,160
You hugged me,

322
00:24:05,200 --> 00:24:07,160
but did you ever love me?

323
00:24:20,800 --> 00:24:22,360
Are you okay, Mr. Rachen?

324
00:24:25,000 --> 00:24:27,440
I've worked with you for three years.

325
00:24:28,640 --> 00:24:30,520
For three years, I've seen you

326
00:24:30,600 --> 00:24:31,760
give everything to Be Rich,

327
00:24:32,440 --> 00:24:34,720
to Mr. Tritot,
without caring about yourself at all.

328
00:24:35,760 --> 00:24:38,200
But what you got back is not fair.

329
00:24:39,320 --> 00:24:41,520
You're talented. You're capable.

330
00:24:42,240 --> 00:24:43,560
You don't need Be Rich

331
00:24:44,080 --> 00:24:46,040
to succeed.

332
00:24:47,000 --> 00:24:49,240
And now Mr. Tritot is gone.

333
00:24:50,160 --> 00:24:52,840
Why don't you try
doing something for yourself for once?

334
00:25:18,520 --> 00:25:19,520
Where are you going, Da?

335
00:25:22,920 --> 00:25:24,840
I don't have the right
to stay here anymore.

336
00:25:26,000 --> 00:25:27,600
Mr. Tritot is gone.

337
00:25:28,200 --> 00:25:30,160
He probably didn't want me
to stay here either.

338
00:25:31,080 --> 00:25:32,440
That's why he wrote the will like that.

339
00:25:34,320 --> 00:25:36,000
Well, I don't mean to kick you out.

340
00:25:37,040 --> 00:25:38,920
But if you're leaving,
I'll have the maids help you move.

341
00:25:44,240 --> 00:25:45,760
Did I do something so wrong?

342
00:25:46,400 --> 00:25:48,040
Is that why your dad hated me so much?

343
00:25:48,880 --> 00:25:50,920
Just because I dated his son?

344
00:25:54,320 --> 00:25:56,840
I lost my good future

345
00:25:57,760 --> 00:25:58,920
because of that accident.

346
00:26:02,600 --> 00:26:04,360
But I tried.

347
00:26:08,280 --> 00:26:12,160
I tried to live what's left of my life
as best as I could.

348
00:26:13,560 --> 00:26:16,040
But every time I wanted to start over,

349
00:26:17,200 --> 00:26:19,720
your dad would yank me back,

350
00:26:20,400 --> 00:26:22,320
crushing my hope.

351
00:26:23,400 --> 00:26:24,760
Is this

352
00:26:24,840 --> 00:26:28,120
what I deserve for having loved you?

353
00:26:37,080 --> 00:26:38,040
I'm sorry, Da.

354
00:26:39,000 --> 00:26:41,360
I know it sounds too late,

355
00:26:42,200 --> 00:26:44,480
but I truly regret
everything that happened.

356
00:26:48,400 --> 00:26:50,240
I don't want your pity

357
00:26:50,840 --> 00:26:52,080
or your contempt.

358
00:26:52,680 --> 00:26:53,800
Then what do you want?

359
00:26:55,240 --> 00:26:56,640
This house?

360
00:26:57,320 --> 00:26:58,160
Money?

361
00:27:00,560 --> 00:27:01,400
A job.

362
00:27:02,040 --> 00:27:03,440
I want a job.

363
00:27:04,040 --> 00:27:05,600
I want to prove to everyone

364
00:27:05,680 --> 00:27:07,760
that I'm capable

365
00:27:08,840 --> 00:27:09,880
of more than…

366
00:27:12,200 --> 00:27:14,680
more than being just a sex object.

367
00:27:23,080 --> 00:27:25,360
Let me work at Be Rich, please.

368
00:27:54,840 --> 00:27:56,320
May I join you?

369
00:27:58,600 --> 00:28:00,080
One Daiquiri, please.

370
00:28:03,520 --> 00:28:05,200
Didn't you say you don't like coming here

371
00:28:05,280 --> 00:28:07,480
because it's an old-people bar?

372
00:28:09,080 --> 00:28:11,200
Well, I want to date an older guy.

373
00:28:14,920 --> 00:28:17,200
Mom already heard about the will.

374
00:28:18,280 --> 00:28:20,560
I see your mom knows everything anyway.

375
00:28:22,680 --> 00:28:24,080
I know

376
00:28:24,800 --> 00:28:27,880
you've been dragging your feet
and refusing to be the new chairman

377
00:28:28,480 --> 00:28:31,160
even though my mom
has been openly backing you so hard

378
00:28:31,720 --> 00:28:33,480
because you were waiting for it.

379
00:28:35,280 --> 00:28:36,800
You were hoping

380
00:28:37,320 --> 00:28:39,840
that the one to hand you that position

381
00:28:41,520 --> 00:28:42,360
would be Uncle Tritot.

382
00:28:45,920 --> 00:28:49,280
You wanted him to be the one
to appoint you chairman.

383
00:28:58,440 --> 00:29:01,000
Go on. Say it
that in the end, he didn't give it to me.

384
00:29:03,720 --> 00:29:04,680
Yes.

385
00:29:05,200 --> 00:29:07,680
And are you really
going to give up that easily?

386
00:29:11,680 --> 00:29:13,200
I've always done everything for Dad.

387
00:29:14,440 --> 00:29:15,760
So if today,

388
00:29:16,800 --> 00:29:19,360
he wanted Trai to own Be Rich,

389
00:29:20,720 --> 00:29:22,280
then I'll allow it for him too.

390
00:29:23,000 --> 00:29:24,240
Rachen,

391
00:29:24,880 --> 00:29:26,640
don't be stupid.

392
00:29:27,720 --> 00:29:29,760
Uncle isn't even here anymore.

393
00:29:29,840 --> 00:29:33,480
Are you going to be filial
to a ghost or something?

394
00:29:38,760 --> 00:29:40,360
You're pretty funny, Mika.

395
00:29:42,440 --> 00:29:45,280
Being a puppet chairman for Mrs. Mookmanee

396
00:29:45,360 --> 00:29:47,400
or being an idiot
still living under Dad's shadow…

397
00:29:49,040 --> 00:29:49,960
I won't know which to choose.

398
00:29:50,600 --> 00:29:53,000
My mom doesn't think of you as a puppet.

399
00:29:53,960 --> 00:29:55,840
The reason she likes you

400
00:29:55,920 --> 00:29:57,240
is because you're good,

401
00:29:57,320 --> 00:29:58,760
because you work well.

402
00:29:58,840 --> 00:30:00,760
The reason she supports you

403
00:30:01,640 --> 00:30:04,160
is because of your own ability.

404
00:30:06,400 --> 00:30:09,160
Did Uncle really make you
look down on yourself this much?

405
00:30:10,040 --> 00:30:13,680
What a shame.
My mom actually believed you could do it.

406
00:30:16,880 --> 00:30:20,240
Tell your mom
I'll go in and talk tomorrow.

407
00:30:21,000 --> 00:30:24,080
I'll talk about appointing
Be Rich's new chairman.

408
00:30:26,560 --> 00:30:29,240
So you chose my mom, then?

409
00:30:31,240 --> 00:30:33,480
Trai shouldn't get anything
from Dad anymore…

410
00:30:35,400 --> 00:30:37,080
especially that chair.

411
00:30:47,960 --> 00:30:49,040
Mr. Trai.

412
00:30:49,120 --> 00:30:51,600
The technician just informed
that nothing can be recovered

413
00:30:51,680 --> 00:30:54,360
from either the laptop or the phone
we sent in for data recovery.

414
00:30:54,440 --> 00:30:55,520
They tried,

415
00:30:55,600 --> 00:30:58,160
but the phone was system-reset,
completely wiped.

416
00:30:58,240 --> 00:30:59,560
And the laptop

417
00:30:59,640 --> 00:31:01,760
had a virus that destroyed everything.

418
00:31:04,760 --> 00:31:07,080
So whatever was
on the laptop or the phone…

419
00:31:08,840 --> 00:31:11,000
got Dad killed, but we don't know what?

420
00:31:14,600 --> 00:31:16,880
And did that kid admit who sent him yet?

421
00:31:17,560 --> 00:31:18,480
Not yet.

422
00:31:19,880 --> 00:31:21,200
But we have something we need to tell you.

423
00:31:25,640 --> 00:31:27,520
On the day you returned to Thailand,

424
00:31:27,600 --> 00:31:30,440
Mr. Tritot started suspecting
that certain shareholders

425
00:31:30,520 --> 00:31:32,680
were using nominees to quietly buy up
small shareholders' stocks.

426
00:31:32,760 --> 00:31:34,040
Who?

427
00:31:34,120 --> 00:31:36,120
Mr. Tritot ordered Ms. Kaew

428
00:31:36,200 --> 00:31:38,320
from the trading compliance team
to investigate.

429
00:31:38,400 --> 00:31:40,280
And he also hired a private investigator

430
00:31:40,880 --> 00:31:43,440
to look into the attempted attack
on you at the school.

431
00:31:45,400 --> 00:31:47,360
Before Mr. Tritot fell down the stairs,

432
00:31:48,080 --> 00:31:51,000
the investigator contacted him
to report the progress,

433
00:31:51,080 --> 00:31:52,720
but we don't know the details

434
00:31:52,800 --> 00:31:56,160
because the investigator agreed
to report only to Mr. Tritot.

435
00:31:56,920 --> 00:31:58,920
Right now, we still
can't reach the investigator.

436
00:31:59,000 --> 00:32:00,960
We heard he went overseas for work.

437
00:32:01,040 --> 00:32:03,040
But we'll do everything we can
to get in touch with him.

438
00:32:04,600 --> 00:32:07,040
So Dad might've died
because of people who hate Be Rich

439
00:32:08,000 --> 00:32:09,760
or because of people who want Be Rich?

440
00:32:18,560 --> 00:32:21,080
I really want to know,
when Dad was sitting in this chair,

441
00:32:22,240 --> 00:32:24,280
who did he piss off so badly?

442
00:32:28,960 --> 00:32:31,120
Once you get info from Ms. Kaew,
tell me right away.

443
00:32:31,200 --> 00:32:32,920
- And reach that investigator.
- Yes, sir.

444
00:32:33,640 --> 00:32:35,760
And you, find a way to check it too.

445
00:32:35,840 --> 00:32:37,440
Hire a pro if you have to.

446
00:32:37,960 --> 00:32:40,720
I need to know
who owns that anti-Be Rich page.

447
00:32:40,800 --> 00:32:41,680
Yes, sir.

448
00:32:44,480 --> 00:32:45,560
Trai.

449
00:32:45,640 --> 00:32:48,320
Someone sent a package to Mr. Tritot.

450
00:32:48,400 --> 00:32:49,680
Don't know what it is. It's heavy.

451
00:32:49,760 --> 00:32:51,840
Uh, Ms. Darin, put it down first, please.

452
00:32:51,920 --> 00:32:54,240
Put it down. Put it down, Ms. Darin.

453
00:32:55,280 --> 00:32:56,760
Why? What is it?

454
00:32:56,840 --> 00:32:58,160
I don't know what it is either.

455
00:32:58,240 --> 00:33:00,160
But with everything going on,
it's better to be careful.

456
00:33:00,880 --> 00:33:02,480
- Mr. Trai.
- Mr. Trai.

457
00:33:05,720 --> 00:33:06,960
- Mr. Trai, no!
- What are you doing?

458
00:34:20,000 --> 00:34:22,719
<i>Trai, happy birthday.</i>

459
00:34:25,600 --> 00:34:27,920
<i>It's kinda embarrassing.</i>
<i>I've never done anything like this.</i>

460
00:34:29,920 --> 00:34:31,040
<i>I'm doing it just for you.</i>

461
00:34:34,040 --> 00:34:35,239
<i>Did you get your birthday present?</i>

462
00:34:36,800 --> 00:34:38,239
<i>Wait. You did, didn't you?</i>

463
00:34:38,840 --> 00:34:40,400
<i>Otherwise, how would you be watching this?</i>

464
00:34:42,120 --> 00:34:43,120
<i>So,</i>

465
00:34:44,199 --> 00:34:46,120
<i>let's look at photos together.</i>

466
00:34:49,000 --> 00:34:51,760
<i>These photos make me really happy.</i>

467
00:34:53,480 --> 00:34:54,320
<i>‪Here.</i>

468
00:34:56,520 --> 00:34:57,360
<i>This one.</i>

469
00:34:59,800 --> 00:35:00,840
<i>You remember this one?</i>

470
00:35:02,280 --> 00:35:03,920
<i>How would you? You were tiny.</i>

471
00:35:05,720 --> 00:35:06,880
<i>This was</i>

472
00:35:08,000 --> 00:35:09,720
<i>the first time I ever held you.</i>

473
00:35:12,120 --> 00:35:13,240
<i>You were so small.</i>

474
00:35:16,640 --> 00:35:17,600
<i>You bit my shoulder.</i>

475
00:35:20,880 --> 00:35:23,720
<i>You were just this little thing.</i>
<i>But back then, to me,</i>

476
00:35:23,800 --> 00:35:25,760
<i>you felt heavy as hell.</i>

477
00:35:26,280 --> 00:35:28,520
<i>I was scared of everything.</i>

478
00:35:29,440 --> 00:35:30,840
<i>Scared I wouldn't raise you right.</i>

479
00:35:30,920 --> 00:35:32,200
<i>Scared you wouldn't</i>

480
00:35:32,800 --> 00:35:34,000
<i>be comfortable in my arms.</i>

481
00:35:34,520 --> 00:35:37,120
<i>Scared I'd bend your arms or legs wrong.</i>

482
00:35:37,800 --> 00:35:39,120
<i>Scared I'd drop you.</i>

483
00:35:40,040 --> 00:35:42,720
<i>I was so tense.</i>
<i>I was tense about everything.</i>

484
00:35:44,280 --> 00:35:46,680
<i>But you were comfortable. You peed on me.</i>

485
00:35:47,200 --> 00:35:49,840
<i>You peed all over me.</i>

486
00:35:51,000 --> 00:35:52,320
<i>And then you smiled at me…</i>

487
00:35:53,600 --> 00:35:55,080
<i>like nothing happened.</i>

488
00:35:57,680 --> 00:36:00,040
<i>It was your first smile.</i>

489
00:36:02,320 --> 00:36:04,680
<i>I still remember it like it was yesterday.</i>

490
00:36:06,840 --> 00:36:09,360
<i>I fell in love with you from that moment.</i>

491
00:36:12,040 --> 00:36:13,680
<i>It was such a beautiful smile.</i>

492
00:36:14,840 --> 00:36:16,080
<i>Smile often, okay?</i>

493
00:36:20,600 --> 00:36:21,680
<i>This one…</i>

494
00:36:22,360 --> 00:36:24,560
<i>It's probably the last photo</i>

495
00:36:25,080 --> 00:36:27,840
<i>of the three of us…</i>

496
00:36:30,360 --> 00:36:31,720
<i>together…</i>

497
00:36:33,680 --> 00:36:35,240
<i>before your mom left.</i>

498
00:36:36,600 --> 00:36:37,600
<i>I miss her.</i>

499
00:36:38,880 --> 00:36:40,600
<i>We didn't take enough pictures.</i>

500
00:36:42,240 --> 00:36:43,760
<i>We should've taken more.</i>

501
00:36:46,440 --> 00:36:49,800
<i>From now on, you and I have</i>
<i>to take lots of pictures,</i>

502
00:36:50,880 --> 00:36:52,880
<i>so we won't regret it like this again.</i>

503
00:36:58,880 --> 00:37:00,920
What do you mean lots of pictures, Dad?

504
00:37:03,240 --> 00:37:05,240
You're not here
to take them with me anymore.

505
00:37:08,600 --> 00:37:10,160
<i>You know what, Trai?</i>

506
00:37:11,600 --> 00:37:13,040
<i>The day…</i>

507
00:37:14,760 --> 00:37:16,320
<i>I thought you were going to die.</i>

508
00:37:18,560 --> 00:37:20,720
<i>The day the school caught fire,</i>

509
00:37:22,080 --> 00:37:23,280
<i>in that moment,</i>

510
00:37:25,640 --> 00:37:27,120
<i>I knew…</i>

511
00:37:28,640 --> 00:37:29,680
<i>that I…</i>

512
00:37:31,680 --> 00:37:33,000
<i>love you so much.</i>

513
00:37:34,280 --> 00:37:36,400
<i>Seriously. I…</i>

514
00:37:37,680 --> 00:37:39,520
<i>I can exchange my life with yours.</i>

515
00:37:40,600 --> 00:37:41,840
<i>I love you.</i>

516
00:37:45,120 --> 00:37:46,800
<i>I didn't want to lose you.</i>

517
00:37:50,760 --> 00:37:52,560
<i>Hey, no, no, no.</i>

518
00:37:52,640 --> 00:37:54,920
<i>It's your birthday.</i>

519
00:37:57,040 --> 00:37:58,640
<i>I just wanted to say</i>

520
00:37:59,680 --> 00:38:01,160
<i>I'm sorry I told you</i>

521
00:38:01,240 --> 00:38:03,000
<i>I love you too late.</i>

522
00:38:05,760 --> 00:38:06,960
<i>I love you, Trai…</i>

523
00:38:08,560 --> 00:38:09,640
<i>so damn much,</i>

524
00:38:11,360 --> 00:38:12,600
<i>you little brat.</i>

525
00:38:23,120 --> 00:38:24,840
I love you too, Dad…

526
00:38:25,760 --> 00:38:27,640
I love you so much.

527
00:38:42,440 --> 00:38:45,880
Dad, I miss you…

528
00:38:46,760 --> 00:38:48,360
I miss you so much…

529
00:38:52,720 --> 00:38:54,560
Let's get straight to the point.

530
00:38:55,840 --> 00:38:57,120
I'd like to nominate Mr. Rachen

531
00:38:57,200 --> 00:38:59,640
as the next leader of Be Rich,

532
00:38:59,720 --> 00:39:02,800
because he is the most qualified
and the most ready.

533
00:39:03,480 --> 00:39:06,080
Does anyone object or would like
to nominate someone else?

534
00:39:07,440 --> 00:39:08,520
We agree.

535
00:39:09,120 --> 00:39:10,640
No one can take care of Be Rich

536
00:39:11,160 --> 00:39:12,480
better than Rachen.

537
00:39:14,720 --> 00:39:16,320
Mr. Rachen, please.

538
00:39:51,040 --> 00:39:52,000
Mr. Rachen.

539
00:39:57,440 --> 00:39:59,480
I'm sorry for calling everyone in
so suddenly.

540
00:39:59,560 --> 00:40:02,520
I have something I'd like to inform you,
but I want to announce it just once.

541
00:40:03,280 --> 00:40:05,480
Is it about Mr. Tritot's death?

542
00:40:06,080 --> 00:40:08,320
- Not exactly.
- Then is it about Be Rich?

543
00:40:10,080 --> 00:40:11,880
I'd like to say it all at once.

544
00:40:11,960 --> 00:40:13,760
Please wait a moment.
They should be here any second.

545
00:40:23,840 --> 00:40:25,760
Ah, perfect timing.

546
00:40:26,840 --> 00:40:29,200
The executive team is all here, right?

547
00:40:29,920 --> 00:40:31,080
Hello. Hello.

548
00:40:42,560 --> 00:40:44,000
What are you trying to stir up now?

549
00:40:46,400 --> 00:40:47,800
I'm not here to stir anything up.

550
00:40:49,920 --> 00:40:51,120
I'm here to announce something.

551
00:40:58,960 --> 00:40:59,840
Everyone.

552
00:41:02,080 --> 00:41:04,480
I, Trai Bowornmongkolphong,

553
00:41:06,080 --> 00:41:07,280
would like to nominate myself

554
00:41:07,360 --> 00:41:09,880
for the position of CEO of Be Rich.

555
00:41:18,960 --> 00:41:21,640
CEO of the company?

556
00:41:30,400 --> 00:41:31,400
What's wrong with you?

557
00:41:31,480 --> 00:41:33,280
Didn't you say you didn't want Be Rich?

558
00:41:33,360 --> 00:41:34,880
Hey, I don't want Be Rich.

559
00:41:34,960 --> 00:41:37,040
I'm just doing this for Dad.

560
00:41:37,880 --> 00:41:38,840
<i>Trai…</i>

561
00:41:40,160 --> 00:41:43,040
<i>I want you to inherit Be Rich after me.</i>

562
00:41:43,120 --> 00:41:45,640
<i>Not because you're my only son,</i>

563
00:41:46,720 --> 00:41:48,280
<i>but because…</i>

564
00:41:50,000 --> 00:41:51,320
<i>you're nothing like me.</i>

565
00:41:52,440 --> 00:41:55,320
<i>And you're nothing</i>
<i>like the people around me either.</i>

566
00:41:55,400 --> 00:41:58,600
<i>I want the company</i>
<i>I built with my own hands</i>

567
00:41:59,680 --> 00:42:02,000
<i>to be in the hands of someone</i>
<i>with a heart like yours.</i>

568
00:42:04,520 --> 00:42:06,400
<i>Someone who understands the value of money</i>

569
00:42:07,320 --> 00:42:09,320
<i>but doesn't become its slave.</i>

570
00:42:12,000 --> 00:42:13,560
<i>I want Be Rich</i>

571
00:42:14,400 --> 00:42:16,000
<i>to grow…</i>

572
00:42:17,960 --> 00:42:19,160
<i>with someone like you.</i>

573
00:42:23,320 --> 00:42:24,520
<i>I'm counting on you, Trai.</i>

574
00:42:26,080 --> 00:42:28,640
You said I've never done
anything for Dad, right?

575
00:42:28,720 --> 00:42:29,560
Here.

576
00:42:30,200 --> 00:42:31,920
This is my first and last time.

577
00:42:33,080 --> 00:42:35,040
You couldn't even take care of Dad.

578
00:42:35,120 --> 00:42:36,720
How are you going to take care of Be Rich?

579
00:42:37,280 --> 00:42:38,600
Dad left Be Rich with me.

580
00:42:39,280 --> 00:42:40,560
I have to do it.

581
00:42:42,160 --> 00:42:44,320
So you're taking everything from me?

582
00:42:45,040 --> 00:42:46,320
But let me tell you something.

583
00:42:47,280 --> 00:42:49,240
This time, it won't be as easy as before.

584
00:42:52,800 --> 00:42:54,360
Even if you hold the most shares,

585
00:42:54,440 --> 00:42:56,680
you're still not the majority vote
in this company.

586
00:42:57,200 --> 00:42:59,720
You can't just appoint yourself
like some dictator.

587
00:42:59,800 --> 00:43:02,280
You can't use the media
to pressure the executives either.

588
00:43:03,640 --> 00:43:05,640
Be Rich's next chairman

589
00:43:06,200 --> 00:43:08,520
must be someone who has worked
for Be Rich all along,

590
00:43:08,600 --> 00:43:10,720
who stood
shoulder to shoulder with Mr. Tritot,

591
00:43:10,800 --> 00:43:12,840
who knows
how the Be Rich system actually works.

592
00:43:12,920 --> 00:43:14,040
I already told you

593
00:43:14,120 --> 00:43:16,440
I'm proposing myself as a candidate.

594
00:43:16,520 --> 00:43:19,040
So I want a fair competition,

595
00:43:19,120 --> 00:43:21,160
a fair election.

596
00:43:21,240 --> 00:43:22,080
It's a waste of time.

597
00:43:22,880 --> 00:43:24,680
We can't let some kid
who refuses to grow up

598
00:43:24,760 --> 00:43:26,040
run our organization.

599
00:43:30,960 --> 00:43:31,840
Why not give Mr. Trai

600
00:43:31,920 --> 00:43:33,960
a chance to prove himself first?

601
00:43:34,040 --> 00:43:35,840
Prove what? A worldview-rejecting talent

602
00:43:36,360 --> 00:43:37,680
with a former escort

603
00:43:38,280 --> 00:43:39,640
as his assistant?

604
00:43:40,160 --> 00:43:41,880
There's nothing left to prove.

605
00:43:47,160 --> 00:43:48,360
I will prove it.

606
00:43:55,160 --> 00:43:58,560
I'll work until everyone can see
that I, Trai,

607
00:43:58,640 --> 00:43:59,880
a completely useless kid,

608
00:44:00,480 --> 00:44:03,000
can still make Be Rich grow strongly.

609
00:44:03,600 --> 00:44:05,520
Please give me one more chance.

610
00:44:37,600 --> 00:44:39,520
MR. TRAI

611
00:44:39,600 --> 00:44:41,040
Excuse me.

612
00:44:41,640 --> 00:44:43,240
Are you delivering
or picking something up?

613
00:44:43,840 --> 00:44:45,840
Uh, I'm here to see…

614
00:44:45,920 --> 00:44:48,640
If you're delivering, leave it downstairs.
No need to go up.

615
00:44:48,720 --> 00:44:50,160
But if you're going up
to pick something up,

616
00:44:50,240 --> 00:44:52,200
you'll need a visitor badge.
Outsiders aren't allowed in.

617
00:44:53,120 --> 00:44:54,920
I'm a friend of…

618
00:45:39,360 --> 00:45:40,960
I'm his friend.

619
00:45:43,240 --> 00:45:45,280
But is he still my friend?

620
00:45:58,160 --> 00:46:00,440
Have you seen this?
Have you seen the news about Trai?

621
00:46:01,080 --> 00:46:02,120
Look.

622
00:46:02,920 --> 00:46:06,080
TRAI IS RUNNING FOR THE CEO POSITION

623
00:46:06,680 --> 00:46:07,520
I saw it.

624
00:46:08,400 --> 00:46:09,280
And?

625
00:46:13,200 --> 00:46:15,640
I got ten orders today!

626
00:46:15,720 --> 00:46:18,600
First day on the job
and I'm already killing it.

627
00:46:18,680 --> 00:46:20,480
Ugh, let's talk about Mr. Trai first.

628
00:46:20,560 --> 00:46:22,400
Come on, let's eat chicken.

629
00:46:22,480 --> 00:46:24,280
I bought fried chicken for everyone.

630
00:46:25,680 --> 00:46:26,600
Hurry up.

631
00:46:44,120 --> 00:46:45,560
I made some fruit juice,

632
00:46:45,640 --> 00:46:46,920
so you'll feel refreshed.

633
00:46:47,960 --> 00:46:49,600
Thanks so much, Da. Just put them there.

634
00:47:01,080 --> 00:47:03,440
Are these people on Mr. Rachen's side?

635
00:47:03,520 --> 00:47:04,640
More or less.

636
00:47:05,160 --> 00:47:06,720
It's Mrs. Mookmanee's group.

637
00:47:08,160 --> 00:47:10,040
One, two, three, four.

638
00:47:10,720 --> 00:47:12,040
Four people.

639
00:47:12,120 --> 00:47:13,480
Add Mr. Rachen,

640
00:47:13,560 --> 00:47:15,280
Mrs. Mookmanee, and Mika, that's seven.

641
00:47:16,160 --> 00:47:18,280
They still outnumber
the people who'll vote for you.

642
00:47:18,360 --> 00:47:20,040
I'll figure something out later.

643
00:47:20,640 --> 00:47:21,680
You should rest, Da.

644
00:47:21,760 --> 00:47:23,280
If I need your help, I'll tell you.

645
00:47:45,960 --> 00:47:49,280
Here, wings for Kanah.

646
00:47:49,360 --> 00:47:50,600
The uncle was about to close the shop,

647
00:47:50,680 --> 00:47:53,200
so he discounted everything.
I bought a ton.

648
00:47:56,760 --> 00:47:57,680
Well?

649
00:47:59,920 --> 00:48:01,440
Dodging the question.

650
00:48:01,520 --> 00:48:03,080
Acting way too cheerful.

651
00:48:03,160 --> 00:48:06,240
And you even bought food for everyone
when it's not a special day.

652
00:48:06,320 --> 00:48:07,440
This is

653
00:48:07,520 --> 00:48:09,200
definitely not normal.

654
00:48:09,280 --> 00:48:10,920
I'm gonna call Trai.

655
00:48:15,800 --> 00:48:16,920
Fine. I won't.

656
00:48:28,720 --> 00:48:30,640
MR. TRAI

657
00:48:30,720 --> 00:48:33,160
It's Mr. Trai…

658
00:48:39,680 --> 00:48:41,360
Since when do you owe Mr. Trai money?

659
00:48:42,360 --> 00:48:43,200
Owe money? What?

660
00:48:43,800 --> 00:48:44,880
Hey.

661
00:48:44,960 --> 00:48:46,520
I've been friends with you forever.

662
00:48:46,600 --> 00:48:49,000
I've never seen you avoid anyone,
except creditors.

663
00:48:49,600 --> 00:48:51,560
And now you're declining his calls,

664
00:48:51,640 --> 00:48:53,920
not picking up. That's dodging, isn't it?

665
00:48:55,840 --> 00:48:57,680
Did Trai do something to you?

666
00:48:57,760 --> 00:48:58,600
Tell me.

667
00:49:00,080 --> 00:49:02,160
Ugh. What could he possibly do to me?

668
00:49:06,560 --> 00:49:08,520
Because he didn't do anything, right?

669
00:49:08,600 --> 00:49:10,520
That's why you're sulking.

670
00:49:10,600 --> 00:49:11,960
I got it.

671
00:49:12,040 --> 00:49:13,960
He didn't tell you
about the company thing,

672
00:49:14,040 --> 00:49:15,600
so you're mad.

673
00:49:16,360 --> 00:49:17,720
Oh, Samlee.

674
00:49:18,320 --> 00:49:20,680
Mad? No way.

675
00:49:20,760 --> 00:49:22,160
My sister

676
00:49:22,240 --> 00:49:25,000
isn't petty like that, right?

677
00:49:26,240 --> 00:49:28,560
Yeah. I'm not petty.

678
00:49:28,640 --> 00:49:30,360
And I don't want to be petty either.

679
00:49:32,560 --> 00:49:33,800
MR. TRAI

680
00:49:40,720 --> 00:49:43,600
- Not petty at all.
- No, my sister is not petty.

681
00:49:43,680 --> 00:49:44,520
Totally normal.

682
00:49:44,600 --> 00:49:46,680
Not petty at all.

683
00:49:46,760 --> 00:49:48,480
Just declining the call, that's all.

684
00:49:50,320 --> 00:49:51,240
Oh?

685
00:49:57,280 --> 00:49:58,720
Why'd she decline?

686
00:49:58,800 --> 00:50:00,360
Maybe she's working.

687
00:50:01,320 --> 00:50:02,840
This late, what work could she have?

688
00:50:06,680 --> 00:50:08,280
She isn't even live selling.

689
00:50:10,240 --> 00:50:11,640
Today, you didn't answer Pakbung's calls

690
00:50:12,480 --> 00:50:13,920
and didn't reply to her texts either.

691
00:50:14,000 --> 00:50:16,240
Yeah. I was busy.

692
00:50:17,120 --> 00:50:18,920
I think it's the same reason.

693
00:50:21,680 --> 00:50:23,080
Pakbung's getting back at me?

694
00:50:23,160 --> 00:50:24,440
I'm not holding a grudge.

695
00:50:24,520 --> 00:50:26,720
I'm not mad. I'm not getting back at him.

696
00:50:26,800 --> 00:50:27,640
It's just…

697
00:50:27,720 --> 00:50:29,440
- Just what?
- Just what?

698
00:50:29,960 --> 00:50:31,720
He's just a friend

699
00:50:31,800 --> 00:50:33,600
not answering calls, not reading texts,

700
00:50:33,680 --> 00:50:35,960
not replying, not caring,
not paying attention…

701
00:50:36,040 --> 00:50:38,760
So why am I this emotional?

702
00:50:40,440 --> 00:50:42,040
It's not okay, you guys.

703
00:50:45,080 --> 00:50:46,600
Because it has gone past just friends.

704
00:50:47,880 --> 00:50:48,800
You

705
00:50:48,880 --> 00:50:50,440
like Mr. Trai.

706
00:50:55,320 --> 00:50:56,680
And if I like him,

707
00:50:57,200 --> 00:50:59,040
but I don't like myself like this,

708
00:50:59,560 --> 00:51:00,920
should I even like him?

709
00:51:04,800 --> 00:51:06,920
I know you're scared.

710
00:51:07,440 --> 00:51:09,760
But you're human, not AI.

711
00:51:09,840 --> 00:51:12,640
Let your heart do its job sometimes.

712
00:51:12,720 --> 00:51:15,200
Love sometimes. Hurt sometimes.

713
00:51:15,280 --> 00:51:16,920
That's just how life is.

714
00:51:17,440 --> 00:51:18,800
True.

715
00:51:19,520 --> 00:51:21,000
But I don't want to get hurt.

716
00:51:21,520 --> 00:51:22,880
Being hurt wastes energy.

717
00:51:23,520 --> 00:51:25,560
I need energy to survive.

718
00:51:25,640 --> 00:51:28,680
My stomach isn't even full, and I still
have to do this dramatic love matter?

719
00:51:29,200 --> 00:51:30,280
I can't.

720
00:51:30,800 --> 00:51:32,320
I'm backing off.

721
00:51:33,080 --> 00:51:34,760
I don't want to fall in too deep.

722
00:51:35,480 --> 00:51:37,240
I'm scared climbing out will be hard.

723
00:51:37,840 --> 00:51:40,960
So that's that, alright? Alright?

724
00:51:41,880 --> 00:51:44,080
- Okay.
- Okay.

725
00:51:45,520 --> 00:51:49,840
No boyfriend,
then we'll stay like this till we're old.

726
00:51:49,920 --> 00:51:52,320
Sure, let's go along with it.

727
00:51:53,000 --> 00:51:55,400
I respect your decision, always.

728
00:51:56,880 --> 00:51:57,760
Alright.

729
00:51:58,280 --> 00:52:00,040
Cheers to single life.

730
00:52:03,680 --> 00:52:05,160
Single, pretty,

731
00:52:05,240 --> 00:52:06,840
when we're rich, we'll buy some.

732
00:52:09,480 --> 00:52:10,640
I mean we'll buy chicken.

733
00:52:13,760 --> 00:52:15,800
Yeah, whatever. Just eat. It's good.

734
00:52:17,360 --> 00:52:18,920
MR. TRAI

735
00:52:20,640 --> 00:52:21,760
Can I have some chicken butt?

736
00:52:21,840 --> 00:52:23,120
Yeah, eat up.

737
00:52:23,200 --> 00:52:25,400
- Let's share.
- Here's the sauce.

738
00:52:25,480 --> 00:52:27,960
- Alright.
- Yummy, huh?

739
00:52:28,040 --> 00:52:29,920
- It's good.
- I know you like it juicy.

740
00:52:30,000 --> 00:52:32,120
It's good. Thank you.

741
00:52:50,000 --> 00:52:53,040
TRAI

742
00:52:55,120 --> 00:52:56,320
Hello, Trai.

743
00:53:08,800 --> 00:53:09,640
- Peekaboo!
- Ah.

744
00:53:10,240 --> 00:53:13,080
- Give me that. Give it.
- Hey. What is this?

745
00:53:16,840 --> 00:53:18,600
I ask nicely, and you won't give.

746
00:53:18,680 --> 00:53:19,680
It has to be like this.

747
00:53:23,040 --> 00:53:24,320
You have money but don't repay me?

748
00:53:24,400 --> 00:53:25,360
- Hey.
- What?

749
00:53:26,120 --> 00:53:27,640
I'll tell you something.

750
00:53:27,720 --> 00:53:29,680
There's a company chairman

751
00:53:29,760 --> 00:53:32,080
who's so rich… her boyfriend.

752
00:53:34,760 --> 00:53:36,280
- Give me my money.
- Hey.

753
00:53:36,360 --> 00:53:37,840
Go ask your boyfriend then.

754
00:53:37,920 --> 00:53:39,360
Why are you taking it out on me?

755
00:53:39,440 --> 00:53:42,360
Or… he dumped her? Oh, my.

756
00:53:42,440 --> 00:53:45,160
A rich-ass man like that,
she should've held on tight.

757
00:53:45,240 --> 00:53:47,360
Here's some advice. Film a video.

758
00:53:47,440 --> 00:53:50,120
When you two… bang-bang…

759
00:53:50,200 --> 00:53:52,160
Bang-bang…

760
00:53:52,240 --> 00:53:53,080
Get evidence.

761
00:53:53,160 --> 00:53:55,560
When he dumps you, pull it out,

762
00:53:55,640 --> 00:53:57,160
so you don't get played for free.

763
00:53:58,200 --> 00:53:59,320
Hey!

764
00:54:00,000 --> 00:54:02,400
You think every woman
is trying to catch a rich man?

765
00:54:02,480 --> 00:54:06,280
You think only rich people get to choose,
and poor people just get dumped forever?

766
00:54:07,240 --> 00:54:09,840
Yeah. Most of the time, that's true.

767
00:54:11,000 --> 00:54:12,480
But I didn't get dumped.

768
00:54:13,280 --> 00:54:14,840
I chose to walk away

769
00:54:14,920 --> 00:54:16,320
because I'm sick of it.

770
00:54:16,840 --> 00:54:20,640
I'm sick of people
who do nothing all day, just being nosy

771
00:54:20,720 --> 00:54:22,800
about who's with who,
who's breaking up with who,

772
00:54:22,880 --> 00:54:24,200
who's banging who.

773
00:54:24,720 --> 00:54:26,480
Listen here.

774
00:54:27,000 --> 00:54:28,800
I don't have a boyfriend.

775
00:54:28,880 --> 00:54:30,480
And I don't have money.

776
00:54:31,080 --> 00:54:32,200
I don't have anything!

777
00:54:35,520 --> 00:54:37,080
Stop coming after me for debt!
Give it here.

778
00:54:43,720 --> 00:54:44,920
Hey,

779
00:54:45,000 --> 00:54:47,120
if you don't stop coming to collect debt,

780
00:54:47,920 --> 00:54:50,360
I'll call you something bad.

781
00:54:51,440 --> 00:54:52,600
Something bad?

782
00:54:53,440 --> 00:54:54,800
What does it mean?

783
00:54:55,400 --> 00:54:58,680
Maybe this. Boss. Bad.

784
00:54:58,760 --> 00:54:59,840
- Bastard!
- Bastard!

785
00:54:59,920 --> 00:55:01,400
Bastard what?

786
00:55:01,480 --> 00:55:02,880
Whoa.

787
00:55:02,960 --> 00:55:04,400
Didn't you go to school?

788
00:55:04,480 --> 00:55:06,320
It's like this.

789
00:55:07,120 --> 00:55:09,960
Boss. Bad.

790
00:55:10,040 --> 00:55:12,080
- Bastard!
- Again?

791
00:55:12,160 --> 00:55:13,880
- Whoa. Let's go.
- Sorry, Boss.

792
00:55:23,200 --> 00:55:26,080
I can get rich on my own.
I don't need to leech off anyone.

793
00:55:26,840 --> 00:55:27,800
Let's go, baby.

794
00:55:28,800 --> 00:55:30,040
Let's go get rich.

795
00:55:34,800 --> 00:55:36,400
Let's go.

796
00:55:45,320 --> 00:55:46,280
Mr. Trai?

797
00:55:49,280 --> 00:55:50,880
You didn't answer my calls, Pakbung.

798
00:55:51,560 --> 00:55:53,880
You blocked my bike
just for this small matter?

799
00:55:53,960 --> 00:55:55,760
You almost died for nothing.

800
00:55:55,840 --> 00:55:57,520
Just a small matter? This is serious.

801
00:55:59,720 --> 00:56:00,560
Are you mad at me?

802
00:56:02,280 --> 00:56:04,320
I'm not mad. Just…

803
00:56:04,400 --> 00:56:05,960
You still don't get it?

804
00:56:06,880 --> 00:56:07,960
What's going on?

805
00:56:08,960 --> 00:56:10,800
Not answering your call
means she doesn't want to talk to you.

806
00:56:11,440 --> 00:56:12,560
It's that simple.

807
00:56:13,680 --> 00:56:16,160
Don't be shallow like your relationships.

808
00:56:16,240 --> 00:56:18,680
What Pakbung and I have
is deeper than that.

809
00:56:18,760 --> 00:56:20,240
Deeper what?

810
00:56:24,280 --> 00:56:26,400
Go back the way you came.
I'm talking to Pakbung.

811
00:56:26,480 --> 00:56:27,680
Why should I?

812
00:56:27,760 --> 00:56:30,040
I came to talk to Pakbung, not you.

813
00:56:30,640 --> 00:56:31,800
I feel so pretty.

814
00:56:32,400 --> 00:56:33,840
Why am I this pretty?

815
00:56:37,720 --> 00:56:38,680
I was here first.

816
00:56:41,480 --> 00:56:43,600
Then let Pakbung decide

817
00:56:43,680 --> 00:56:45,000
who she wants to talk to.

818
00:56:50,560 --> 00:56:51,520
I have to choose?

819
00:56:59,320 --> 00:57:00,880
Let money decide then.

820
00:57:05,560 --> 00:57:08,240
Whoever pays more wins.

821
00:57:08,320 --> 00:57:11,080
Anyone transferring? You?

822
00:57:12,200 --> 00:57:13,320
You?

823
00:57:14,120 --> 00:57:16,440
No? Then I'm going to work.

824
00:57:23,600 --> 00:57:24,800
20,000 BAHT

825
00:57:26,160 --> 00:57:27,880
20,000?

826
00:57:27,960 --> 00:57:29,040
Just one hour.

827
00:57:29,120 --> 00:57:31,600
- Hey, Pakbung's not for sale.
- I am.

828
00:57:32,840 --> 00:57:34,040
Pakbung!

829
00:57:34,120 --> 00:57:35,800
But there's a line.

830
00:57:35,880 --> 00:57:37,000
I already have a client

831
00:57:37,080 --> 00:57:38,440
who booked earlier.

832
00:57:38,520 --> 00:57:39,960
If you can wait, wait.

833
00:57:40,040 --> 00:57:41,960
If not, no refunds.

834
00:57:43,400 --> 00:57:44,640
Bye.

835
00:58:12,880 --> 00:58:15,000
<i>I want to compete with you</i>
<i>fair and square.</i>

836
00:58:15,080 --> 00:58:17,560
<i>Let the results speak for themselves.</i>

837
00:58:17,640 --> 00:58:19,480
I'm honestly thrilled

838
00:58:19,560 --> 00:58:21,240
that he finally died.

839
00:58:22,920 --> 00:58:27,160
You took Dad's leftovers.
Now, get ready to take mine too, Trai.

840
00:58:27,920 --> 00:58:29,280
How the hell can you say that?!

841
00:58:29,360 --> 00:58:30,280
How can you say that?!

842
00:58:30,360 --> 00:58:31,520
How can you say that?!

843
00:58:31,600 --> 00:58:32,720
Fine dining or BBQ?

844
00:58:32,800 --> 00:58:33,960
- BBQ.
- Mall or market?

845
00:58:34,040 --> 00:58:35,800
- Market.
- Gambling or working?

846
00:58:35,880 --> 00:58:37,480
- Working.
- Mr. Rachen or Trai?

847
00:58:37,560 --> 00:58:38,880
Trai.

848
00:58:43,600 --> 00:58:46,280
<i>I won't throw money at you</i>
<i>like Rachen does.</i>

849
00:58:46,360 --> 00:58:47,800
<i>Then what will you throw at me?</i>

850
00:58:47,880 --> 00:58:48,920
<i>Don't tell me…</i>

851
00:58:49,000 --> 00:58:50,440
Your body?

852
00:58:51,360 --> 00:58:52,400
No, don't.

853
00:58:52,920 --> 00:58:55,240
So you've been avoiding me
because you're afraid of your own heart.

854
00:58:55,320 --> 00:58:58,360
- Afraid of what?
- You're afraid of loving me, aren't you?

855
00:58:58,880 --> 00:59:00,160
You really think we can just be friends?

856
00:59:00,240 --> 00:59:01,160
I guess so.

857
00:59:47,440 --> 00:59:52,800
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
